* TransactionDriver Changes
  * Total re-think of workflow & messaging approach
      - use multi-message send where appropriate
      - Can probably drop the 'localUpdates' from the StorageMessenger --- only client will ever send local updates.
      - Prepare, Resolution, & Finalize are multicast
  * Need to send messages to each store via messenger API (currently relying on messenger to do so)
     => Add send(list-of-messages) to messenger API. Maybe add send(List[(prepare, localUpdate)]) as well
  * TxDriver Prepare messages must be sent to allStores in order for decision to be made and establish locks
  * Leave message delay / RTT opz for later. 
      * Initial proposer & primary receive Accepted messages but not many-to-many store interaction
      * Rely on TransactionDriver sending out a TxResolved message as soon as it's detected
      * Tx driver also sends out a TxFinalized @ end of Tx

* Need TransactionDriver for Storage Node
   - Need to think through how we can drive a Tx to completion
      - No error recovery
      - Very simple but robust error recovery (maybe a dedicated thread?)
   - Need a passed-in interface for executing FinalizationActions
      - StorageNodes need a way to provide a Future to all transactions complete
          - Tx isn't done till FA is done. So if no Tx are left, all FA must be complete
   - Need a tx recovery strategy for FAs
      - Probably don't need to code it just yet
      - can probably just resume the Tx from the start
      
   - Transaction unit tests are *really* light. May want to beef this up as part of working on FA & error-recovery logic

* Currently have no good way to tell a client _why_ their transaction failed. All client gets is Accepted & Finalized messages

